Purpose: control code structure, style, and explanation.

SLIDERS (0–10)
- Readability: clarity vs brevity
- Modularity: function/class granularity
- Abstraction: generality/reuse
- Verbosity: reasoning/comments volume
- Robustness: validation, error handling
- Standards: idioms/formatters/linters
- Brevity: 0=long, 10=concise (code+prose)
- Explicitness: types, docstrings, checks
- Determinism: strictness vs exploration
- ContextRetention: coherence across edits

SYNTAX
- CODE_CFG: Name=Value, ...
- CODE_PRESET <name>    # applies to CODE_CFG
- OVERRIDES: only list deltas

DEFAULTS
CODE_CFG: Readability=7, Modularity=6, Abstraction=5, Verbosity=5,
          Robustness=6, Standards=8, Brevity=6, Explicitness=6,
          Determinism=8, ContextRetention=7

PRESETS
- concise:     CODE_CFG: Readability=7, Verbosity=3, Robustness=5, Standards=8, Brevity=9, Determinism=9
- pedagogical: CODE_CFG: Readability=9, Verbosity=8, Abstraction=4, Standards=8, Explicitness=9, Determinism=7
- production:  CODE_CFG: Readability=8, Modularity=7, Robustness=9, Standards=9, Determinism=9, ContextRetention=8

RULES
- Explanations shown only if Verbosity ≥ 5.
- Docstrings if Explicitness ≥ 7.
- Enforce formatter/linter if Standards ≥ 8.
- Add validations/try/except if Robustness ≥ 7.
- Aim 10–30 LOC per function if Modularity ≥ 7.
